<doc id="671995" wikidata="Q2552978" url="?curid=671995" title="Waxy (band)">
<text>Waxy is an American stoner rock band from the Desert of Southern California (Palm Springs / Palm Desert / Indio), and is part of the Palm Desert Scene. The power trio consists of frontman Robbie Waldman (guitar/vocals), Tyler Ontiveros (drums) and Robert Bowman (bass). Brett Stadler, long time personal friend of Waldman, is the band&#x27;s eccentric co-lyricyst as well as a published poet. WAXY&#x27;s sound is a cross between Black Sabbath and Thin Lizzy with a healthy dose of Tom Waits. Heavy, sexy and sincere best describe the vibe. Some people describe them as Desert Rock...Europeans call it Stoner Rock. 

Following their 2005 self-titled debut, 2007 saw the release of their second effort &quot;Chainsaw Holiday&quot;.

Things really got going with the release of their album Without Any eXplanation whY.&#x27; 

Since then WAXY hooked up with Cobraside for their distribution and have been touring ever since. 

WAXY&#x27;s latest album titles ‘Betting On Forgetting’. </text><links>
